<div id="review_2379373017" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2379373017" />
    <a title="chantel nouseforaname" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24627290-chantel-nouseforaname"><img alt="chantel nouseforaname" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1531190305p2/24627290.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2379373017?book_show_action=true">May 01, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="chantel nouseforaname" class="user" itemprop="url" name="chantel nouseforaname" href="/user/show/24627290-chantel-nouseforaname">chantel nouseforaname</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24627290-chantel-nouseforaname?shelf=later-in-life-reads">later-in-life-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24627290-chantel-nouseforaname?shelf=heavy">heavy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24627290-chantel-nouseforaname?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24627290-chantel-nouseforaname?shelf=women-of-color-writers">women-of-color-writers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24627290-chantel-nouseforaname?shelf=black-women-writers">black-women-writers</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2379373017" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5861184725721742164">What an ending! I didn’t see it coming, but it did feel like Lutie Johnson (the main character) was teetering on the edge since page one and I guess they pushed her too many times. I feel like The Street relates so much so to the here and now. It’s 70 years later and has many things changed? Not really. <br/><br/>This book was an excercise in how not to lose your mind; but it’s so much more than that. It’s about how microaggressions and racism can push a woman to the extreme ends of sanity and rage.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


