<div id="review_2938144887" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2938144887" />
    <a title="Lisa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8051792-lisa"><img alt="Lisa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1544530609p2/8051792.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2938144887?book_show_action=true">Aug 20, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lisa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lisa" href="/user/show/8051792-lisa">Lisa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8051792-lisa?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2938144887" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6804316464369968003">A blurb on the back cover of my edition calls The Street &quot;as much a historical document as it is a novel&quot;. I think that is accurate. The novel records the corrosive effects of racism, poverty and sexism on Lutie Johnson, a single mother, living in Harlem in the mid 1940s. The grim existence of Lutie and others on the street is unrelenting - and left me reeling.</span>
  <span id="freeText6804316464369968003" style="display:none">A blurb on the back cover of my edition calls The Street "as much a historical document as it is a novel". I think that is accurate. The novel records the corrosive effects of racism, poverty and sexism on Lutie Johnson, a single mother, living in Harlem in the mid 1940s. The grim existence of Lutie and others on the street is unrelenting - and left me reeling.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6804316464369968003" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review2938144887">
